commit.message:
Add note for LuaJIT 5.2 style containers

If you use the LUAJIT_ENABLE_LUA52COMPAT compilation flag with LuaJIT, C++ container can be used just fine with `ipairs` or `pairs` as these properly check the metatable keys `__ipairs` and `__pairs` used by sol to implement this behaviour.

üõ† Address lifetime issues through Lua references in iterators.

‚Äî üìù Fixes #1315, #1374, and #1400.
‚Äî üìù Lifetime in iterators was referencing the wrong stack (the main thread) rather than the coroutine's stack at time of creation.
‚Äî üìù Using main_reference/main_* objects was a suitable enough fix for most of these problems.
‚Äî ‚ö°üõ† Prevent performance and usability issues from changing containers by storing the being/end iterator separately, rather than continually invoking `deferred_uc::end(‚Ä¶)` every time.
‚Äî üõ† Improve sizes for stored iterators in select cases.
‚Äî üõ† Allow for sentinel-style C++20-and-beyond ranges.
‚Äî üîß Improve single file generation CMake.
‚Äî üë∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Fix up internal Lua build system issues.
Fix get_max_hp mehod in property example
Add mention of sol2::sol2 alias in build.rst
Fixed possible typo.
üõ† Review exhaustive check and get rid of a few Wall/pedwarn warnings
üõ† Fix exhaustive checking compilation
‚ú® New exhaustive check feature for vectors & similar

Fix clang compiler warning

[why]
Compiling with clang issues this warning (clang 10.0 and 15.0 tested):

    .../sol/sol.hpp:14541:32: warning: unknown warning group '-Wmaybe-uninitialized', ignored [-Wunknown-warning-option]
    #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wmaybe-uninitialized"

[how]
Check if the compiler does know the warning, before trying to turn the
warning off.

commit.message: Fix compile error when registering new user types with operator()

CMake: Build LuaJIT: use copy_if_different

Use copy_if_different to move luajit products in the post build step to
avoid relinking of projects depending on sol2/luagit.
This is mostly relevant when building sol2 and luajit as subprojects.
